1
00:00:02,078 --> 00:00:03,113
Hello.

2
00:00:03,179 --> 00:00:06,149
I'm Yoo Byungjae, a quiet man
hosting The Quiet Interview.

3
00:00:07,117 --> 00:00:11,721
Today's guest has a smile
that feels like a warm spring day.

4
00:00:11,788 --> 00:00:16,359
It's the kind of smile that could melt
the frozen Hangang River.

5
00:00:16,426 --> 00:00:19,362
But when that smile fades,

6
00:00:19,429 --> 00:00:24,267
it can make the air turn icy,
letting a chill settle in.

7
00:00:24,935 --> 00:00:27,504
Will a spring breeze
fill the studio today,

8
00:00:27,571 --> 00:00:29,472
or will the chill of winter take over?

9
00:00:29,539 --> 00:00:32,642
Let's quietly welcome our guest.

10
00:00:46,289 --> 00:00:47,357
Hello.

11
00:00:51,494 --> 00:00:52,562
Hello.

12
00:00:55,765 --> 00:00:56,833
Where is it?

13
00:01:05,208 --> 00:01:06,209
Hello.

14
00:01:07,510 --> 00:01:08,645
Hello.

15
00:01:09,746 --> 00:01:10,881
Hello.

16
00:01:31,835 --> 00:01:36,539
Could you please take a look
at the audience members?

17
00:01:36,606 --> 00:01:40,777
They came all this way just for you, Chuu.

18
00:01:41,912 --> 00:01:44,481
Some of them look familiar.

19
00:01:44,548 --> 00:01:46,349
Hello, I'm Chuu.

20
00:01:46,416 --> 00:01:49,586
Nice to meet you.
Thank you so much for coming.

21
00:01:49,653 --> 00:01:51,988
YUCHAN CAN PROTECT CHUU
PROTECT MY HEART, CHUU

22
00:01:54,024 --> 00:01:55,792
This is amazing.

23
00:01:58,428 --> 00:02:05,035
Chuu actually joined us
on <i>No-Laughing Birthday Party </i>before.

24
00:02:05,101 --> 00:02:06,102
I did.

25
00:02:06,169 --> 00:02:07,971
The Quiet Interview is a bit different.

26
00:02:08,038 --> 00:02:11,641
-So let me go over the rules with you.
-Yes, please.

27
00:02:11,708 --> 00:02:13,543
It's simple. You can't laugh.

28
00:02:13,610 --> 00:02:16,813
These cameras in front of us
aren't just any cameras.

29
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:19,583
They're equipped with
a cutting-edge AI detection system.

30
00:02:19,649 --> 00:02:20,650
What?

31
00:02:20,717 --> 00:02:26,823
They detect in real-time
whether you're smiling or laughing.

32
00:02:26,890 --> 00:02:30,927
If you let out a giggle,
you'll hear a warning sound.

33
00:02:30,994 --> 00:02:32,162
A warning sound?

34
00:02:32,662 --> 00:02:34,731
-I see.
-You'll hear that sound.

35
00:02:34,798 --> 00:02:39,035
And if it's clear to everyone
that you've burst out laughing,

36
00:02:39,102 --> 00:02:42,906
a much louder siren will go off.

37
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:54,684
We have our "siren guy" here on set,
assisting with that.

38
00:02:54,751 --> 00:02:55,752
Okay.

39
00:02:55,819 --> 00:02:57,554
Once the siren goes off,

40
00:02:57,621 --> 00:03:00,457
you'll be sent to the Quiet Room
for five minutes,

41
00:03:00,523 --> 00:03:04,160
where you'll spend
a lonely and isolated time.

42
00:03:04,227 --> 00:03:05,228
-Me?
-Yes.

43
00:03:05,295 --> 00:03:08,498
-I see.
-And if I happen to laugh,

44
00:03:08,565 --> 00:03:10,800
you'll be able to come back and join us.

45
00:03:10,867 --> 00:03:12,969
So your strategy could be
to make me laugh.

46
00:03:13,036 --> 00:03:14,204
Got it.

47
00:03:14,271 --> 00:03:17,540
As I've mentioned before,
I'm a huge fan of yours.

48
00:03:17,607 --> 00:03:19,743
And I've been watching
<i>Chuu Can Do It </i>for ages.

49
00:03:19,809 --> 00:03:21,811
I remember almost every little moment.

50
00:03:21,878 --> 00:03:24,748
What I love most is
how the show inspires people

51
00:03:24,814 --> 00:03:28,785
to protect the environment
and care for the planet.

52
00:03:28,852 --> 00:03:30,387
Thank you so much.

53
00:03:30,453 --> 00:03:33,156
Have you been practicing
what you learned on the show?

54
00:03:33,223 --> 00:03:35,025
Yes, I have.

55
00:03:35,091 --> 00:03:39,195
My parents and friends
put a lot of it into practice as well.

56
00:03:39,262 --> 00:03:42,065
-Some friends keep it up to this day.
-Really?

57
00:03:42,132 --> 00:03:45,101
We were so inspired by your channel

58
00:03:45,168 --> 00:03:49,105
that we've made
The Quiet Interview eco-friendly too.

59
00:03:49,172 --> 00:03:52,509
-Do you see the person on the bicycle?
-Yes.

60
00:03:52,576 --> 00:03:54,978
-The lighting and the cameras on set…
-I see.

61
00:03:55,045 --> 00:03:58,949
…are currently being powered
by that bicycle generator.

62
00:03:59,015 --> 00:04:00,517
-Really?
-Yes.

63
00:04:00,584 --> 00:04:03,019
It's something we felt strongly about.

64
00:04:03,086 --> 00:04:06,289
The Earth and every living creature on it

65
00:04:06,356 --> 00:04:08,758
-are truly precious.
-Right.

66
00:04:08,825 --> 00:04:10,160
That's why… Hey, you!

67
00:04:10,227 --> 00:04:11,228
Hey!

68
00:04:11,728 --> 00:04:13,697
I'm sorry.

69
00:04:14,431 --> 00:04:15,432
Good.

70
00:04:22,305 --> 00:04:23,940
I'm so sad.

71
00:04:26,243 --> 00:04:27,410
I was actually crying.

72
00:04:30,180 --> 00:04:31,281
Hey.

73
00:04:32,015 --> 00:04:33,016
-Hey!
-Yo!

74
00:04:33,083 --> 00:04:35,051
-Yes?
-The Earth is hurting.

75
00:04:35,118 --> 00:04:36,786
It's hurting.

76
00:04:36,853 --> 00:04:38,722
-So push through the pain.
-Push.

77
00:04:39,623 --> 00:04:40,690
Keep pedaling.

78
00:04:43,293 --> 00:04:44,294
Faster.

79
00:04:44,861 --> 00:04:46,363
Faster!

80
00:04:46,429 --> 00:04:47,664
So it was true.

81
00:04:52,269 --> 00:04:55,639
Welcome to the eco-friendly talk show,
The Quiet Interview.

82
00:04:55,705 --> 00:04:57,440
Chuu is our guest for today.

83
00:04:57,507 --> 00:05:00,143
The warning sound went off earlier.

84
00:05:00,210 --> 00:05:05,081
I know you laugh a lot
and always have a smile on your face.

85
00:05:05,148 --> 00:05:09,719
So, for the first time ever,
we've prepared a special segment for you.

86
00:05:09,786 --> 00:05:10,954
What kind…

87
00:05:11,021 --> 00:05:13,323
-What did you just say?
-What kind of rule?

88
00:05:13,390 --> 00:05:15,225
You see, I…

89
00:05:19,162 --> 00:05:20,363
No! What do I do?

90
00:05:20,430 --> 00:05:22,032
-You're okay for now.
-Really?

91
00:05:24,601 --> 00:05:26,269
It's okay to laugh now.

92
00:05:26,336 --> 00:05:30,807
We've prepared a special segment
where you can laugh as much as you want.

93
00:05:30,874 --> 00:05:34,711
So for this segment,
we've invited a comedian

94
00:05:34,778 --> 00:05:38,381
whose jokes land perfectly every time.

95
00:05:38,448 --> 00:05:42,786
We'll give you some time
to just sit back and laugh at his jokes.

96
00:05:42,852 --> 00:05:44,120
-Okay.
-Where is he?

97
00:05:44,187 --> 00:05:46,590
I'm right here. Hello.

98
00:05:46,656 --> 00:05:47,958
-Hello.
-All right.

99
00:05:48,658 --> 00:05:50,827
-Should I start?
-Yes, go ahead.

100
00:05:53,597 --> 00:05:55,665
What's the opposite of a stand-up cop?

101
00:05:55,732 --> 00:05:57,267
A dirty cop?

102
00:05:58,268 --> 00:05:59,369
A sit-down cop.

103
00:05:59,936 --> 00:06:01,738
-I see.
-Okay.

104
00:06:04,841 --> 00:06:08,678
What happens if Chuu gets electrocuted?

105
00:06:08,745 --> 00:06:10,280
Pikachuu!

106
00:06:10,881 --> 00:06:12,549
-You knew that one.
-Yes!

107
00:06:15,685 --> 00:06:19,155
That was just a joke.
We don't want you to get electrocuted.

108
00:06:20,824 --> 00:06:23,760
-I'm thinking of going to Japan.
-Okay.

109
00:06:23,827 --> 00:06:27,864
I'm planning to go to Fukuoka.
Just going to Fuku-soak in the culture.

110
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:32,302
That was Choi Useon.

111
00:06:35,839 --> 00:06:37,574
Goodbye, everyone.

112
00:06:39,843 --> 00:06:43,513
That wraps up this segment.
Now the no-laugh rule is in full effect.

113
00:06:43,580 --> 00:06:45,549
Let's talk about what's new with you.

114
00:06:45,615 --> 00:06:48,952
From music to variety shows to dramas,

115
00:06:49,019 --> 00:06:52,455
you've truly been active
across the board this year.

116
00:06:52,522 --> 00:06:55,025
You even took on
a serious acting role this time.

117
00:06:55,091 --> 00:06:56,760
-Is that right?
-Yes.

118
00:06:56,826 --> 00:07:00,397
<i>-My Girlfriend Is The Man!</i>
-Yes, it aired on KBS.

119
00:07:00,463 --> 00:07:02,465
Thanks to your performance,

120
00:07:02,532 --> 00:07:05,068
the show recorded
a remarkable 13.1% viewership,

121
00:07:05,135 --> 00:07:07,938
-an impressive feat in this OTT era.
-What?

122
00:07:08,004 --> 00:07:10,674
-Wait.
-I don't think it was 13.1%.

123
00:07:11,241 --> 00:07:12,509
-My apologies.
-Yes.

124
00:07:13,109 --> 00:07:14,277
Sorry, one second.

125
00:07:16,213 --> 00:07:18,148
What? "Add it up"?

126
00:07:18,215 --> 00:07:19,716
What do you mean?

127
00:07:21,851 --> 00:07:24,354
-How many episodes were there?
-Twelve episodes.

128
00:07:24,421 --> 00:07:25,488
"Add it up"?

129
00:07:27,324 --> 00:07:29,993
You can't say it like that.
What were you thinking?

130
00:07:30,060 --> 00:07:31,061
Seriously.

131
00:07:31,127 --> 00:07:33,196
Just because the ratings weren't great…

132
00:07:33,263 --> 00:07:35,131
No show gets 13% these days.

133
00:07:36,266 --> 00:07:37,601
Yeah, that's crazy.

134
00:07:38,201 --> 00:07:42,272
So you added up
all 12 episodes to get 13.1%?

135
00:07:43,106 --> 00:07:44,107
Okay.

136
00:07:44,174 --> 00:07:45,375
She's laughing!

137
00:07:46,676 --> 00:07:47,744
Are you laughing?

138
00:07:49,179 --> 00:07:52,749
Let's talk about your variety shows.
You're a regular on so many.

139
00:07:52,816 --> 00:07:56,887
You've got your channel, <i>Chuu Can Do It,</i>
and you were also on <i>Steel Troops.</i>

140
00:07:58,288 --> 00:08:01,491
They received so much love,
and I enjoyed watching them too.

141
00:08:01,558 --> 00:08:05,128
-Really?
-Yes. You were also on <i>The Devil's Plan…</i>

142
00:08:05,795 --> 00:08:06,796
One second.

143
00:08:10,634 --> 00:08:12,903
Why did you write this?
What's wrong with you?

144
00:08:15,672 --> 00:08:18,708
Did you do the research?
She wasn't on <i>The Devil's Plan.</i>

145
00:08:19,342 --> 00:08:21,678
-I was on it briefly.
-Hey.

146
00:08:22,445 --> 00:08:24,948
I watched that show twice,
from beginning to end.

147
00:08:25,949 --> 00:08:28,285
-I was on it.
-I watched it twice.

148
00:08:31,888 --> 00:08:33,256
I only went to pee once.

149
00:08:35,859 --> 00:08:37,594
This is ridiculous.

150
00:08:43,733 --> 00:08:46,570
I must have appeared
when you went to the bathroom.

151
00:08:46,636 --> 00:08:49,873
I apologize,
it seems there was a slight error.

152
00:08:49,940 --> 00:08:52,509
But rules are rules,
so please head to the Quiet Room.

153
00:08:52,576 --> 00:08:53,643
-Me?
-Yes.

154
00:08:53,710 --> 00:08:56,546
I just want to make it clear
that I did appear on the show.

155
00:08:56,613 --> 00:08:58,348
You must've peed for a long time.

156
00:08:58,415 --> 00:09:01,618
I was on the first and second episodes.

157
00:09:05,355 --> 00:09:10,093
Unfortunately, our guest has been confined
to the Quiet Room.

158
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:12,429
But our show must go on.

159
00:09:12,495 --> 00:09:16,800
We anticipated this situation
and invited a substitute in advance.

160
00:09:16,866 --> 00:09:20,203
This person is bright, bubbly,
and has puppy-like features,

161
00:09:20,270 --> 00:09:21,671
just like Chuu.

162
00:09:21,738 --> 00:09:23,139
Really? Who is it?

163
00:09:23,907 --> 00:09:27,711
They asked to be introduced
as the "Second Chuu."

164
00:09:27,777 --> 00:09:28,778
Who is it?

165
00:09:28,845 --> 00:09:30,380
Let's welcome them.

166
00:09:39,055 --> 00:09:40,223
No way!

167
00:09:40,724 --> 00:09:42,559
Hello, I'm Chuu.

168
00:09:42,626 --> 00:09:43,660
What? No!

169
00:09:43,727 --> 00:09:45,095
Thanks for coming today.

170
00:09:45,161 --> 00:09:46,897
Good to see you, Chuu.

171
00:09:46,963 --> 00:09:48,565
That's not Chuu.

172
00:09:50,233 --> 00:09:55,038
I feel like I'd get in trouble
if I don't ask you to do this.

173
00:09:55,105 --> 00:09:59,109
Could you show the viewers
your iconic "biting heart"?

174
00:10:05,715 --> 00:10:06,716
That's great.

175
00:10:06,783 --> 00:10:08,685
-No.
-Let's keep it going.

176
00:10:08,752 --> 00:10:11,421
Could you show us
the viral "Frozen Cat Challenge"?

177
00:10:12,822 --> 00:10:14,491
Oh, my goodness.

178
00:10:14,558 --> 00:10:17,360
A cat walks across
the frozen Hangang River.

179
00:10:22,299 --> 00:10:25,468
A cat walks across
the frozen Hangang River.

180
00:10:32,509 --> 00:10:33,677
Final question.

181
00:10:34,678 --> 00:10:36,413
You just had a smoke, didn't you?

182
00:10:38,515 --> 00:10:41,151
-I'm Chuu, so--
-No.

183
00:10:41,218 --> 00:10:43,653
You just smoked a cigarette, right?

184
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:46,056
Well…

185
00:10:46,122 --> 00:10:48,525
-I'm just--
-I'm asking because I can smell it.

186
00:10:48,592 --> 00:10:49,893
Yes, I did.

187
00:10:51,861 --> 00:10:55,131
Sorry, but we can't have smokers here.
Please go back to your seat.

188
00:10:55,198 --> 00:10:56,199
Thank you.

189
00:11:02,038 --> 00:11:04,874
It's been five minutes,
so you can come back.

190
00:11:04,941 --> 00:11:06,810
I'm the real Chuu.

191
00:11:06,877 --> 00:11:08,478
-Yes, please come back.
-Okay.

192
00:11:08,545 --> 00:11:09,813
Thank you.

193
00:11:10,380 --> 00:11:14,951
We weren't trying to collect
heartwarming stories about you,

194
00:11:15,018 --> 00:11:20,223
but someone on our crew said
they worked with you before

195
00:11:20,290 --> 00:11:22,592
-and had a good story to share.
-Really?

196
00:11:22,659 --> 00:11:25,629
Do you recognize anyone here?

197
00:11:25,695 --> 00:11:26,796
Yes.

198
00:11:26,863 --> 00:11:28,531
-I see.
-I know him.

199
00:11:29,499 --> 00:11:31,534
He worked as a producer on <i>Chuu Can Do It…</i>

200
00:11:31,601 --> 00:11:33,303
-I know.
-…and now works with us.

201
00:11:33,370 --> 00:11:34,871
-Do you remember him?
-Of course.

202
00:11:34,938 --> 00:11:36,606
I recognized him right away.

203
00:11:36,673 --> 00:11:40,277
Please start by introducing yourself
and then share your story.

204
00:11:40,343 --> 00:11:43,079
-He wrote a letter.
-Really?

205
00:11:46,149 --> 00:11:48,885
Hi, I'm Park Sanghyeok,
a former producer on <i>Chuu Can Do It.</i>

206
00:11:48,952 --> 00:11:51,321
Park Sanghyeok! Sorry.

207
00:11:51,821 --> 00:11:55,425
Chuu is the most professional celebrity
I have ever met.

208
00:11:55,492 --> 00:11:56,526
Really?

209
00:11:56,593 --> 00:11:59,296
When I would nap during breaks on set,

210
00:11:59,362 --> 00:12:01,898
she'd personally go and buy me hot coffee.

211
00:12:01,965 --> 00:12:03,400
-What?
-You're very kind.

212
00:12:03,466 --> 00:12:06,369
Looking after the crew
during shoots isn't easy.

213
00:12:06,436 --> 00:12:10,140
I've read a lot of comments
that talk about how nice you are.

214
00:12:10,206 --> 00:12:12,275
She poured the hot coffee on my thigh.

215
00:12:14,044 --> 00:12:17,414
When I screamed,
she kicked me in the shin a few times

216
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:20,183
to remind me we were on set.

217
00:12:23,186 --> 00:12:24,821
CHUU WOULD NEVER DO THAT!

218
00:12:24,888 --> 00:12:28,225
-Chuu always carried a magnifying glass.
-How cute.

219
00:12:28,291 --> 00:12:31,061
She would use it to burn ants
when shoots ran long.

220
00:12:32,495 --> 00:12:34,331
Then one day, she said we had to film

221
00:12:34,397 --> 00:12:37,567
a sequel to the "Frozen Cat Challenge,"
but with a dog this time.

222
00:12:37,634 --> 00:12:42,739
She told me to fetch a golden retriever
and freeze the Hangang River.

223
00:12:42,806 --> 00:12:43,974
I see.

224
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:45,642
It was August.

225
00:12:45,709 --> 00:12:48,311
I managed to find a dog,

226
00:12:48,378 --> 00:12:51,681
but since it was a labrador retriever
and not a golden retriever,

227
00:12:51,748 --> 00:12:55,619
she hit me with brass knuckles,
leaving me with short-term memory loss.

228
00:12:55,685 --> 00:12:56,686
Oh, dear.

229
00:12:56,753 --> 00:13:02,592
Despite his short-term memory loss,
he came here to share this story.

230
00:13:02,659 --> 00:13:04,060
So let's give him a hand.

231
00:13:04,127 --> 00:13:08,531
How is this a heartwarming story?
Also, that was all a lie.

232
00:13:09,032 --> 00:13:10,433
Was it a lie?

233
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:13,003
-Yes, it was.
-Which part?

234
00:13:13,069 --> 00:13:16,406
The only true thing he said was
that he was a producer on <i>Chuu Can Do It.</i>

235
00:13:16,473 --> 00:13:20,610
But he said you were the most
professional celebrity he's ever met.

236
00:13:20,677 --> 00:13:22,479
I'm not a professional.

237
00:13:22,979 --> 00:13:25,715
I'm still an ama-Chuu-r.

238
00:13:27,851 --> 00:13:31,021
All right, thank you for clearing that up.

239
00:13:32,889 --> 00:13:33,890
Yes?

240
00:13:35,559 --> 00:13:37,093
Do you have more to say?

241
00:13:38,695 --> 00:13:42,198
Hi, I'm Park Sanghyeok,
a former producer on <i>Chuu Can Do It.</i>

242
00:13:42,265 --> 00:13:45,802
Chuu is the most professional celebrity
I have ever met.

243
00:13:46,303 --> 00:13:48,905
-When I would nap during breaks on set…
-What?

244
00:13:48,972 --> 00:13:50,040
…she'd personally--

245
00:13:50,106 --> 00:13:51,441
-We…
-What's going on?

246
00:13:51,508 --> 00:13:53,176
Maybe you should try again later.

247
00:13:53,243 --> 00:13:55,145
Sorry about that.

248
00:13:56,012 --> 00:13:58,615
Let's continue with the questions.

249
00:13:58,682 --> 00:14:03,153
One of the reasons I became
such a big fan of yours

250
00:14:03,220 --> 00:14:06,523
is because of your bright,
